					</div>
				

				

		  
					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>Working on the assumption that I've got a hangover that actually lets me get out of bed without the bed swaying violently and/or honking into a carrier bag (yeah, been there. A sad day in my life)<br>For starters, I recommend some sugary fizzy drink - ginger beer for preference, as the ginger calms an upset stomach.<br>Then go for a sauna if you can find one, I know they're not on everyone's doorstep. Do a hot/cold changeover several times.<br>Once you've sweated it out, then have some spicy food (I like having Nandos', with the Peri-Peri sauce in the black bottle, for the challenge). <br>An afternoon nap will then top things off nicely, or some brisk exercise. Then promise myself never to drink like that again, until next time.</p>
						
					</div>
				</li>
				
